  "prompt": "What exactly is Gusto?",
  "response": "Gusto is a cloud-based payroll, benefits, and human resource management platform designed primarily for small to medium-sized businesses (SMBs). The platform simplifies various HR tasks by offering a comprehensive suite of tools, including:\n\n1. **Payroll Processing**: Gusto automates payroll calculations, tax withholdings, and direct deposits for employees. It helps ensure compliance with federal, state, and local tax regulations.\n\n2. **Benefits Administration**: Gusto provides options for health insurance, retirement plans, and other employee benefits. Employers can manage benefits enrollment and contributions through the platform.\n\n3. **Employee Onboarding**: The platform streamlines the onboarding process for new hires, allowing businesses to manage paperwork, tax forms, and employee information easily.\n\n4. **Time Tracking**: Gusto offers tools to track employee hours and manage time-off requests, which can integrate directly with payroll.\n\n5. **HR Support**: The platform provides resources for HR compliance, employee handbooks, and other HR-related tasks, often including access to professional HR guidance.\n\nGusto aims to simplify and automate many administrative HR functions, allowing business owners to focus more on their core operations. It has gained popularity among small businesses due to its user-friendly interface and comprehensive features.",
